knowl.intro:
        {{#scenario}}
            {{#phrasing1}}

{{name}} runs a landscaping company. They charge



{{slope}} per hour for labor and


a design fee of {{intercept}}.


Find a linear function which computes the total cost of the landscaping project C(x) (in dollars) if the job takes x hours to complete. Then use that model to answer the following questions. 



What is the fixed cost?


What is the cost for each additional hour?


What is the cost of the landscaping if it takes them {{input}} hours?

            {{/phrasing1}}

            {{#phrasing2}}

{{name}} needs to rent a trench digger. An equipment rental company charges



{{slope}} per day plus


a non-refundable insurance cost of {{intercept}} to rent the digger.


Find a linear function which computes the total cost of renting the digger C(x) (in dollars), for x days. Then use that model to answer the following questions. 



What is the fixed cost?


What is the cost for each additional day?


What is the cost of the rental if it takes them {{input}} days?

            {{/phrasing2}}

            {{#phrasing3}}

{{name}} has a monthly cell phone plan that charges



{{slope}} per minute on the phone plus


a service fee of {{intercept}}.


Find a linear function which computes the total monthly cost of the cell phone C(x) (in dollars), if {{name}} uses it for x minutes. Then use that model to answer the following questions. 



What is the fixed cost?


What is the cost for each additional minute on the phone?


What is the monthly cost of the cell phone if {{name}} uses it for {{input}} minutes?

            {{/phrasing3}}
        {{/scenario}}


{{Prompt}}

knowl.outtro:
        {{#scenario}}
            {{#phrasing1}}

The linear model is C(x) = {{model}}.



The fixed cost is {{intercept}}.


The cost of each additional hour is {{slope}}.


If the job takes {{input}} hours, it will cost {{output}}.

            {{/phrasing1}}

            {{#phrasing2}}

The linear model is C(x) = {{model}}.



The fixed cost is {{intercept}}.


The cost of each additional hour is {{slope}}.


To rent the digger for {{input}} days, it will cost {{output}}.

            {{/phrasing2}}

            {{#phrasing3}}

The linear model is C(x) = {{model}}.



The fixed cost is {{intercept}}.


The cost of each additional minute is {{slope}}.


If {{name}} uses the phone for {{input}} minutes, the monthly cost will be {{output}}.

            {{/phrasing3}}
        {{/scenario}}
